## Plan Summary

**Root cause:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// BUGGY — stops one iteration early, last item is never processed
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// FIXED — processes all items including the last
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**What happens with the bug:**
- `["hello", "world", "foo"]` → returns `["HELLO", "WORLD"]` (misses `"FOO"`)
- `["test"]` → returns `[]` (loop never runs because `0 < 0` is false)

**The fix:** Remove `- 1` from the loop condition in `src/utils.ts` line 7. That's it — a single-token change.

**Verification:** Run `npm test` (Vitest) — all 4 `processItems` test cases should pass after the fix.
